<body>
    <h1>Agent-Agnostic Git State Hook Processor</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p><strong>Status:</strong> Proposal <br><strong>Owner:</strong> <a=
 class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-account-id=3D"626beb05c72f=
140069fcd908" href=3D"https://bitloops.atlassian.net/wiki/people/626beb05c7=
2f140069fcd908?ref=3Dconfluence" target=3D"_blank" data-linked-resource-id=
=3D"131073" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D=
"userinfo" data-base-url=3D"https://bitloops.atlassian.net/wiki">Vasilis Da=
nias</a> <br><strong>Last updated:</strong> <time datetime=3D"2026-03-07" c=
lass=3D"date-past">07 Mar 2026</time></p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Agent-AgnosticGitStateHookProcessor-Objective">Objective</h2>
<p>Implement a <strong>robust, agent-agnostic hook processing system</stron=
g> in the Bitloops Rust CLI that reliably detects meaningful repository mut=
ations triggered by AI agents (Claude, Cursor, Gemini, OpenCode, etc.) and =
executes repository automation logic (e.g., checkpoint branch creation).</p=
>
<p>The design must:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Avoid relying on <strong>agent tool names</strong> (e.g., <code>Edit</co=
de>, <code>Bash</code>, <code>Task</code>)</p></li>
<li>
<p>Work consistently across <strong>multiple agent environments</strong></p=
></li>
<li>
<p>Prevent false triggers caused by:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>temporary edits</p></li>
<li>
<p>reverted edits</p></li>
<li>
<p>repeated hook invocations</p></li>
<li>
<p>non-mutating commands</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p>Instead, the system should detect <strong>Git repository state transitio=
ns</strong>.</p>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"Agent-AgnosticGitStateHookProcessor-CoreDesignPrinciple">Core Des=
ign Principle</h1>
<p>Agent hook events are treated as <strong>signals that a repository mutat=
ion may have occurred</strong>, not proof that one occurred.</p>
<p>The authoritative source of truth is the <strong>Git repository state</s=
trong>.</p>
<p>All hook events route to a <strong>single Rust event processor</strong> =
that inspects Git state and decides whether to execute automation logic.</p=
>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"Agent-AgnosticGitStateHookProcessor-HighLevelArchitecture">High L=
evel Architecture</h1>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Agent H=
ook
   =E2=94=82
   =E2=96=BC
Vendor Adapter (Rust CLI command)
   =E2=94=82
   =E2=96=BC
Git State Processor
   =E2=94=82
   =E2=96=BC
Decision Engine
   =E2=94=82
   =E2=96=BC
Actions (branch creation, checkpoints, metadata updates)</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>The Git state processor is responsible for determining whether the repos=
itory meaningfully changed between hook invocations.</p>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"Agent-AgnosticGitStateHookProcessor-HookInvocationModel">Hook Inv=
ocation Model</h1>
<p>Each vendor hook configuration should invoke the same CLI entrypoint:</p=
>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">bitloop=
s hooks dispatch &lt;vendor&gt; &lt;event&gt;</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Example:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">bitloop=
s hooks dispatch claude post-tool-use
bitloops hooks dispatch claude session-start
bitloops hooks dispatch cursor file-save</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>The Rust CLI normalizes these inputs and forwards them to the <strong>Gi=
t state processor</strong>.</p>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"Agent-AgnosticGitStateHookProcessor-RepositoryStateInspection">Re=
pository State Inspection</h1>
<p>The processor gathers three pieces of Git state:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">HEAD co=
mmit
current branch
working tree status</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Equivalent shell commands:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">git rev=
-parse HEAD
git branch --show-current
git status --porcelain</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>These values describe the entire mutable repository state.</p>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"Agent-AgnosticGitStateHookProcessor-RepositoryFingerprint">Reposi=
tory Fingerprint</h1>
<p>A fingerprint is computed to detect whether the repository changed since=
 the last hook execution.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">fingerp=
rint =3D sha256(
  HEAD
  + branch
  + git status --porcelain
)</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>If the fingerprint matches the previously stored fingerprint, the event =
is ignored.</p>
<p>This eliminates duplicate hook processing.</p>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"Agent-AgnosticGitStateHookProcessor-PersistentHookState">Persiste=
nt Hook State</h1>
<p>Hook state must be persisted to disk.</p>
<p>Recommended location:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">.bitloo=
ps/metadata/hook-state.json</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Suggested structure:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">{
  "last_fingerprint": "...",
  "last_head": "...",
  "branch_created": false
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>This state allows the processor to determine:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>whether the repository changed</p></li>
<li>
<p>whether the change has already been handled</p></li>
<li>
<p>whether a checkpoint branch has already been created</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"Agent-AgnosticGitStateHookProcessor-MutationDetectionLogic">Mutat=
ion Detection Logic</h1>
<p>A mutation is considered meaningful if either:</p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>The working tree changed</p></li>
</ol>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">git sta=
tus --porcelain not empty</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>or</p>
<ol start=3D"2">
<li>
<p>A commit occurred</p></li>
</ol>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">HEAD ch=
anged since previous invocation</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"Agent-AgnosticGitStateHookProcessor-ChangeHandlingAlgorithm">Chan=
ge Handling Algorithm</h1>
<p>Pseudo-logic for the processor:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">load pe=
rsistent hook state

current_state =3D inspect git repo
current_fingerprint =3D hash(current_state)

if current_fingerprint =3D=3D state.last_fingerprint
    exit (duplicate hook)

files_changed =3D working tree status not empty
head_changed =3D state.last_head !=3D current_state.head

if !files_changed &amp;&amp; !head_changed
    update fingerprint
    save state
    exit

if !state.branch_created
    if current branch is not checkpoint/*
        create checkpoint branch
        mark branch_created

update stored fingerprint
update last_head
persist state</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"Agent-AgnosticGitStateHookProcessor-RustImplementationOutline">Ru=
st Implementation Outline</h1>
<h2 id=3D"Agent-AgnosticGitStateHookProcessor-RepositoryStateStructure">Rep=
ository State Structure</h2>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">struct =
RepoState {
    head: String,
    branch: String,
    status: String,
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Agent-AgnosticGitStateHookProcessor-FingerprintCalculation">Finge=
rprint Calculation</h2>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">use sha=
2::{Digest, Sha256};

fn fingerprint(state: &amp;RepoState) -&gt; String {
    let input =3D format!("{}
{}
{}", state.head, state.branch, state.status);
    let mut hasher =3D Sha256::new();
    hasher.update(input);
    format!("{:x}", hasher.finalize())
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Agent-AgnosticGitStateHookProcessor-GitStateInspection">Git State=
 Inspection</h2>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">fn repo=
_state() -&gt; RepoState {
    RepoState {
        head: git("rev-parse HEAD"),
        branch: git("branch --show-current"),
        status: git("status --porcelain"),
    }
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Where <code>git()</code> is a small helper invoking the Git CLI.</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Agent-AgnosticGitStateHookProcessor-PersistentState">Persistent S=
tate</h2>
<p>Use <code>serde</code> + <code>serde_json</code>.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#[deriv=
e(Serialize, Deserialize, Default)]
struct HookState {
    last_fingerprint: Option&lt;String&gt;,
    last_head: Option&lt;String&gt;,
    branch_created: bool,
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>State file path:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">.bitloo=
ps/metadata/hook-state.json</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"Agent-AgnosticGitStateHookProcessor-CheckpointBranchCreation">Che=
ckpoint Branch Creation</h1>
<p>Branch creation should occur only once per session.</p>
<p>Example naming:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">checkpo=
int/&lt;timestamp&gt;</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Rust example:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">fn crea=
te_checkpoint_branch() {
    let name =3D format!("checkpoint/{}", chrono::Utc::now().timestamp());
    git(&amp;format!("checkout -b {}", name));
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Safeguard:</p>
<p>Do not create a checkpoint if already on a checkpoint branch.</p>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"Agent-AgnosticGitStateHookProcessor-HandlingTemporaryEdits">Handl=
ing Temporary Edits</h1>
<p>Example scenario:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">agent e=
dits file
agent reverts file</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>State transitions:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">clean =
=E2=86=92 dirty =E2=86=92 clean</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Final fingerprint equals the baseline fingerprint.</p>
<p>Result:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">no acti=
on executed</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>This prevents creating branches for temporary or reverted edits.</p>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"Agent-AgnosticGitStateHookProcessor-HandlingCommits">Handling Com=
mits</h1>
<p>If an agent commits changes, the working tree may be clean but <code>HEA=
D</code> will change.</p>
<p>This is detected by:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">last_he=
ad !=3D current_head</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Optional: determine which files changed using:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">git dif=
f --name-only &lt;previous_head&gt; &lt;current_head&gt;</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"Agent-AgnosticGitStateHookProcessor-DebouncingRapidEdits(Optional=
)">Debouncing Rapid Edits (Optional)</h1>
<p>Agents sometimes perform multiple edits in quick succession.</p>
<p>To avoid reacting to intermediate states:</p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>detect state change</p></li>
<li>
<p>sleep for ~200ms</p></li>
<li>
<p>re-check repository state</p></li>
<li>
<p>process only if state stabilized</p></li>
</ol>
<p>This can be implemented with <code>std::thread::sleep</code>.</p>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"Agent-AgnosticGitStateHookProcessor-VendorHookConfigurationStrate=
gy">Vendor Hook Configuration Strategy</h1>
<p>Hook configurations should trigger broadly.</p>
<p>Example Claude configuration:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">PostToo=
lUse(Edit)
PostToolUse(Bash)
PostToolUse(Write)</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>All should dispatch to the same CLI command.</p>
<p>Example:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">bitloop=
s hooks dispatch claude post-tool-use</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>The Rust processor decides whether anything meaningful happened.</p>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"Agent-AgnosticGitStateHookProcessor-AdvantagesofThisDesign">Advan=
tages of This Design</h1>
<h3 id=3D"Agent-AgnosticGitStateHookProcessor-AgentAgnostic">Agent Agnostic=
</h3>
<p>Works with:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Claude</p></li>
<li>
<p>Cursor</p></li>
<li>
<p>Gemini</p></li>
<li>
<p>OpenCode</p></li>
<li>
<p>any future agent</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Agent-AgnosticGitStateHookProcessor-Deterministic">Deterministic<=
/h3>
<p>Uses Git state rather than agent heuristics.</p>
<h3 id=3D"Agent-AgnosticGitStateHookProcessor-Robust">Robust</h3>
<p>Handles:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>reverted edits</p></li>
<li>
<p>repeated hook events</p></li>
<li>
<p>Bash edits</p></li>
<li>
<p>direct Git commits</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Agent-AgnosticGitStateHookProcessor-MinimalComplexity">Minimal Co=
mplexity</h3>
<p>Implementation is ~150 lines of Rust.</p>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"Agent-AgnosticGitStateHookProcessor-FutureExtensions">Future Exte=
nsions</h1>
<p>Potential improvements include:</p>
<h3 id=3D"Agent-AgnosticGitStateHookProcessor-WorktreeFingerprint">Worktree=
 Fingerprint</h3>
<p>Track a separate fingerprint for <code>git status --porcelain</code> to =
isolate working tree mutations.</p>
<h3 id=3D"Agent-AgnosticGitStateHookProcessor-SessionTracking">Session Trac=
king</h3>
<p>Track per-agent session IDs for more advanced automation.</p>
<h3 id=3D"Agent-AgnosticGitStateHookProcessor-FileFilters">File Filters</h3=
>
<p>Trigger actions only for changes within certain paths.</p>
<p>Example:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">src/**
*.md</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Agent-AgnosticGitStateHookProcessor-StructuredLogging">Structured=
 Logging</h3>
<p>Emit structured JSON logs describing hook decisions.</p>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"Agent-AgnosticGitStateHookProcessor-Conclusion">Conclusion</h1>
<p>This proposal introduces a <strong>Git state=E2=80=93based hook processo=
r</strong> implemented in Rust that:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>eliminates reliance on fragile tool matchers</p></li>
<li>
<p>works across multiple AI coding agents</p></li>
<li>
<p>reliably detects meaningful repository mutations</p></li>
<li>
<p>prevents false triggers from transient edits</p></li>
</ul>
<p>By using <strong>repository fingerprints and persistent state</strong>, =
the Bitloops CLI can deterministically respond to agent-driven changes whil=
e remaining vendor-independent.</p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
